VOLUMES REPRESENT CHEVRON’S SHARE OF PRODUCTION BY AFFILIATES, INCLUDING TENGIZCHEVROIL IN KAZAKHSTAN AND PETROBOSCAN, PETROINDEPENDIENTE AND PETROPIAR IN VENEZUELA.

4

VOLUMES INCLUDE NATURAL GAS CONSUMED IN OPERATIONS OF 586 MILLION AND 582 MILLION CUBIC FEET PER DAY IN 2012 AND 2011, RESPECTIVELY. TOTAL “AS SOLD” NATURAL GAS VOLUMES WERE 4,488 MILLION AND 4,359 MILLION CUBIC FEET PER DAY FOR 2012 AND 2011, RESPECTIVELY.

