OTHER CONTINGENCIES AND COMMITMENTS

INCOME TAXES

THE COMPANY CALCULATES ITS INCOME TAX EXPENSE AND LIABILITIES QUARTERLY. THESE LIABILITIES GENERALLY ARE SUBJECT TO AUDIT AND ARE NOT FINALIZED WITH THE INDIVIDUAL TAXING AUTHORITIES UNTIL SEVERAL YEARS AFTER THE END OF THE ANNUAL PERIOD FOR WHICH INCOME TAXES HAVE BEEN CALCULATED. REFER TO NOTE 14, BEGINNING ON PAGE FS-43, FOR A DISCUSSION OF THE PERIODS FOR WHICH TAX RETURNS HAVE BEEN AUDITED FOR THE COMPANY’S MAJOR TAX JURISDICTIONS AND A DISCUSSION FOR ALL TAX JURISDICTIONS OF THE DIFFERENCES BETWEEN THE AMOUNT OF TAX BENEFITS RECOGNIZED IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND THE AMOUNT TAKEN OR EXPECTED TO BE TAKEN IN A TAX RETURN. AS DISCUSSED ON PAGE FS-45, CHEVRON IS CURRENTLY ASSESSING THE POTENTIAL IMPACT OF A DECISION BY THE U.S. COURT OF APPEALS FOR THE THIRD CIRCUIT THAT DISALLOWS THE HISTORIC REHABILITA-

